# ANTLR & Stream Language

Grammar file (only place to change syntax):

`maestro-parser/src/main/antlr4/dev/vepo/maestro/parser/Stream.g4`

## Pipeline

```
Stream.g4 → ANTLR generates lexer/parser/listener (target/)
         → StreamQueriesBuilder (listener, hand-written)
         → StreamTopologyParser.parse(String) → StreamModel
```

Never edit generated files. Rebuild: `mvn -pl maestro-parser generate-sources test`.

## Canonical syntax (from docs/samples.md)

```
FROM topic
|> FILTER WHERE expr
|> PROJECT fields: f1, f2
|> MAP SET f1 = expr, f2 = expr
|> WINDOW TUMBLING SIZE 5 MINUTES
|> GROUP BY f1, f2
|> AGGREGATE count(*) AS alias, avg(f) AS alias
|> JOIN users ON orders.user_id = users.id LOOKUP TABLE 'users'
|> BRANCH CASE WHEN … |> TO topic, DEFAULT |> TO topic
|> PATTERN … DETECT AS alias
|> SESSIONIZE BY user_id GAP 30 MINUTES
|> TO sink1, sink2
```

Stages chain with `|>` (`PIPE`). Keywords are case-insensitive. Comments: `-- …`

## Builder pattern (`StreamQueriesBuilder`)

- Extends generated `StreamBaseListener` (listener, not visitor)
- Builds `SourcePipeline` (source + processing stages) and collects `ToStage` sink topics
- Entry point for parsing: `StreamTopologyParser.stream()` only

## Invalid syntax agents often invent (reject)

| Wrong | Correct |
|-------|---------|
| `\|> WHERE x = 1` | `\|> FILTER WHERE x = 1` |
| `\|> TRANSFORM f = expr` | `\|> MAP SET f = expr` |
| `\|> JOIN WITH topic ON a = b` | `\|> JOIN topic ON a = b LOOKUP TABLE 't'` |
| `TO sink1; TO sink2` | `\|> TO sink1, sink2` (single pipeline) |

Copy syntax from `docs/samples.md` and `SamplesParseTest`, not legacy engine tests.
